tplinkVoiceVlanMIB.name: tplinkVoiceVlanMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

tplinkVoiceVlanMIB.description: Private MIB for voice vlan configuration.

voiceVlanGlobalEnable.name: voiceVlanGlobalEnable
voiceVlanGlobalEnable.description: Select Enable/Disable Voice VLAN function. 0. disable 1. enable

voiceVlanId.name: voiceVlanId
voiceVlanId.description: Enter the VLAN ID of the voice VLAN,2-4094.

voiceVlanAgingTime.name: voiceVlanAgingTime
voiceVlanAgingTime.description: Specifies the living time of the member port in auto mode after the OUI address is aging out,1-43200 minute.

voiceVlanPriority.name: voiceVlanPriority
voiceVlanPriority.description: Select the priority of the port when sending voice data. 0. Cos0 1. Cos1 2. Cos2 3. Cos3 4. Cos4 5. Cos5 6. Cos6 7. Cos7

voiceVlanPortTable.name: voiceVlanPortTable
voiceVlanPortTable.description: Here you can configure the parameters of the ports in the voice VLAN..

voiceVlanPortEntry.name: voiceVlanPortEntry
voiceVlanPortEntry.description: An entry contains of the information of port param.

voiceVlanPortNumber.name: voiceVlanPortNumber
voiceVlanPortNumber.description: Displays the port number of the Switch.

voiceVlanPortMode.name: voiceVlanPortMode
voiceVlanPortMode.description: Select the mode for the port to join the voice VLAN. 0. manual: In this mode, you can manually add a port to the voice VLAN or remove a port from the voice VLAN 1. auto: In this mode, the switch automatically adds a port to the voice VLAN or removes a port from the voice VLAN by checking whether the port receives voice data or not.

voiceVlanPortSecurity.name: voiceVlanPortSecurity
voiceVlanPortSecurity.description: Configure the security mode for forwarding packets. 0. disable:All packets are forwarded. 1. enable:Only voice data are forwarded.

voiceVlanPortStatus.name: voiceVlanPortStatus
voiceVlanPortStatus.description: Displays the state of the port in the current voice VLAN. 0. inactive 1. active

voiceVlanPortLag.name: voiceVlanPortLag
voiceVlanPortLag.description: Displays the LAG number which the port belongs to.

voiceVlanOuiConfigTable.name: voiceVlanOuiConfigTable
voiceVlanOuiConfigTable.description: The switch determines whether a received packet is a voice packet by checking its source MAC address. If the source MAC addresses of packets comply with the OUI (organizationally unique identifier) addresses configured by the system, the packets are recognized as voice packets and transmitted in voice VLAN.

voiceVlanOuiConfigEntry.name: voiceVlanOuiConfigEntry
voiceVlanOuiConfigEntry.description: An entry contains of the information of a voice vlan oui.

voiceVlanOui.name: voiceVlanOui
voiceVlanOui.description: Enter the OUI address of the voice device.

voiceVlanOuiMask.name: voiceVlanOuiMask
voiceVlanOuiMask.description: Enter the OUI address mask of the voice device.

voiceVlanDescription.name: voiceVlanDescription
voiceVlanDescription.description: Give a description to the OUI for identification,1-16 characters.

voiceVlanRowStatus.name: voiceVlanRowStatus
voiceVlanRowStatus.description: the following two values are states: these values may be read or written active(1), notInService(2), the following value is a state: this value may be read, but not written notReady(3), the following three values are actions: these values may be written, but are never read createAndGo(4), createAndWait(5), destroy(6)
